desync_mitigation_mode.description: Determines how the load balancer handles requests that might pose a security risk to an application due to HTTP desync. Valid values are `monitor`, `defensive` (default), `strictest`

dns_record_client_routing_policy.description: Indicates how traffic is distributed among the load balancer Availability Zones. Possible values are any_availability_zone (default), availability_zone_affinity, or partial_availability_zone_affinity. Only valid for network type load balancers.

drop_invalid_header_fields.description: Indicates whether HTTP headers with header fields that are not valid are removed by the load balancer (`true`) or routed to targets (`false`). The default is `true`. Elastic Load Balancing requires that message header names contain only alphanumeric characters and hyphens. Only valid for Load Balancers of type `application`

enable_cross_zone_load_balancing.description: If `true`, cross-zone load balancing of the load balancer will be enabled. For application load balancer this feature is always enabled (`true`) and cannot be disabled. Defaults to `true`

enable_deletion_protection.description: If `true`, deletion of the load balancer will be disabled via the AWS API. This will prevent Terraform from deleting the load balancer. Defaults to `true`

enable_http2.description: Indicates whether HTTP/2 is enabled in application load balancers. Defaults to `true`

enable_tls_version_and_cipher_suite_head.description: Indicates whether the two headers (`x-amzn-tls-version` and `x-amzn-tls-cipher-suite`), which contain information about the negotiated TLS version and cipher suite, are added to the client request before sending it to the target. Only valid for Load Balancers of type `application`. Defaults to `false`

enable_waf_fail_open.description: Indicates whether to allow a WAF-enabled load balancer to route requests to targets if it is unable to forward the request to AWS WAF. Defaults to `false`

enable_xff_client_port.description: Indicates whether the X-Forwarded-For header should preserve the source port that the client used to connect to the load balancer in `application` load balancers. Defaults to `false`

enforce_security_group_inbound_rules_on_.description: Indicates whether inbound security group rules are enforced for traffic originating from a PrivateLink. Only valid for Load Balancers of type network. The possible values are on and off.

idle_timeout.description: The time in seconds that the connection is allowed to be idle. Only valid for Load Balancers of type `application`. Default: `60`

internal.description: If true, the LB will be internal. Defaults to `false`

ip_address_type.description: The type of IP addresses used by the subnets for your load balancer. The possible values are `ipv4` and `dualstack`

ipam_pools.description: The IPAM pools to use with the load balancer

listeners.description: Map of listener configurations to create

load_balancer_type.description: The type of load balancer to create. Possible values are `application`, `gateway`, or `network`. The default value is `application`

minimum_load_balancer_capacity.description: Minimum capacity for a load balancer. Only valid for Load Balancers of type `application` or `network`

name.description: The name of the LB. This name must be unique within your AWS account, can have a maximum of 32 characters, must contain only alphanumeric characters or hyphens, and must not begin or end with a hyphen

name_prefix.description: Creates a unique name beginning with the specified prefix. Conflicts with `name`

preserve_host_header.description: Indicates whether the Application Load Balancer should preserve the Host header in the HTTP request and send it to the target without any change. Defaults to `false`

flow_log_destination_type.description: Type of flow log destination. Can be s3 or cloud-watch-logs

igw_tags.description: Additional tags for the internet gateway

instance_tenancy.description: A tenancy option for instances launched into the VPC

intra_route_table_tags.description: Additional tags for the intra route tables

intra_subnet_tags.description: Additional tags for the intra subnets

manage_default_vpc.description: Should be true to adopt and manage Default VPC

map_public_ip_on_launch.description: Should be false if you do not want to auto-assign public IP on launch

nat_eip_tags.description: Additional tags for the NAT EIP

nat_gateway_tags.description: Additional tags for the NAT gateways

nfw_kms_key_arn.description: ARN of the KMS key to use for NFW encryption

one_nat_gateway_per_az.description: Should be true if you want only one NAT Gateway per availability zone. Requires `var.azs` to be set, and the number of `public_subnets` created to be greater than or equal to the number of availability zones specified in `var.azs`.

private_eks_tags.description: A map of tags to add to all privage subnets resources to support EKS

private_route_table_tags.description: Additional tags for the private route tables

propagate_private_route_tables_vgw.description: Should be true if you want route table propagation

propagate_public_route_tables_vgw.description: Should be true if you want route table propagation

public_eks_tags.description: A map of tags to add to all public subnets resources to support EKS

public_route_table_tags.description: Additional tags for the public route tables

redshift_route_table_tags.description: Additional tags for the redshift route tables

redshift_subnet_group_name.description: Optional custom resource name for the Redshift subnet group

redshift_subnet_group_tags.description: Additional tags for the redshift subnet group

redshift_subnet_tags.description: Additional tags for the redshift subnets

resource_prefix.description: Prefix to be added to resource names as identifier

reuse_nat_ips.description: Should be true if you don't want EIPs to be created for your NAT Gateways and will instead pass them in via the 'external_nat_ip_ids' variable

s3_access_logs_bucket.description: bucket id for s3 access logs bucket

s3_kms_key_arn.description: Customer KMS Key id for Cloudwatch Log encryption

secondary_cidr_blocks.description: List of secondary CIDR blocks to associate with the VPC to extend the IP Address pool

single_nat_gateway.description: Should be true if you want to provision a single shared NAT Gateway across all of your private networks

subnet_az_mapping.description: Optional explicit mapping of subnets to AZs - defaults to distributing across AZs

tags.description: A map of tags to add to all resources

tgw_route_table_tags.description: Additional tags for the tgw route tables

vpc_endpoint_security_groups.description: Map of security groups to create for VPC endpoints

vpc_endpoints.description: Map of VPC endpoint definitions to create

vpc_name.description: Name to assign to the AWS VPC

vpn_gateway_custom_name.description: Specifies a custom name to assign to the VPN; if not set, a name will be generated from var.resource_prefix

vpn_gateway_id.description: ID of VPN Gateway to attach to the VPC

vpn_gateway_tags.description: Additional tags for the VPN gateway

admin_ip.description: The public IP address allowed to SSH into the bastion host (CIDR notation).

app_instance_count.description: The number of application server instances to deploy.

instance_type.description: The EC2 instance size for both bastion and application hosts.

region.description: The AWS region to deploy resources into.

vpc_cidr.description: The CIDR block for the VPC.

vpc_name.description: The name of the VPC and prefix for associated resources.
